Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.82,0:00:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, today’s text\Nis a partial quote
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.19,0:00:06.43,Default,,0,0,0,,of Hebrews 13:7.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.42,0:00:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don’t we read the entire verse,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.09,0:00:11.33,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we’ll discuss its importance
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.33,0:00:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to those to whom Paul was writing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.40,0:00:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but also to us today?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.70,0:00:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s Hebrews 13:7:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.97,0:00:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“Remember those who are taking 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.94,0:00:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“the lead among you,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.41,0:00:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“who have spoken the word of God to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.61,0:00:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,“and as you contemplate\Nhow their conduct turns out,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.38,0:00:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,imitate their faith.”
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.55,0:00:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, to whom was Paul writing?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.22,0:00:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, to the Hebrew or Jewish Christians
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.89,0:00:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,who belonged\Nto the congregation in Jerusalem.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.89,0:00:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Was it important for them
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.43,0:00:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to pay attention to those taking the lead?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.47,0:00:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, consider,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.50,0:00:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul wrote this around 61 C.E.,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.24,0:00:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,so that was about five years before Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.98,0:01:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,was surrounded by Roman armies
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.41,0:01:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and then later destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.28,0:01:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, who were taking the lead
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.78,0:01:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Jerusalem congregation at that time?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.92,0:01:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The May 15, 1997, {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}W{\r}{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}atchtower, 
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.29,0:01:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,pages 16 and 17,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.89,0:01:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,explains that it appears\Nthat the governing body,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.90,0:01:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,composed of the remaining members\Nof the apostles and older men,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.90,0:01:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,was likely very active in Jerusalem
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.01,0:01:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,right up until 66 C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.58,0:01:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So surely they would be\Namong ‘those taking the lead’
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.58,0:01:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to whom Paul referred.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.35,0:01:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what things\Ncould the brothers remember
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.82,0:01:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,about the faith and the conduct\Nof the apostles and older men?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.53,0:01:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, they could remember the words
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.53,0:01:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and the example of the apostle Peter.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.60,0:01:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Though Peter was arrested and beaten,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.94,0:02:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,he, along with the rest of the apostles,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.50,0:02:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,told the authorities:
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.67,0:02:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“We must obey God as ruler rather than men.”
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.55,0:02:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And Peter remained active\Nfor the rest of his life,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.98,0:02:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,encouraging the brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.98,0:02:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,They could remember the loyalty
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.25,0:02:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and the courage of the apostle James,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.69,0:02:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,who Herod Agrippa I
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.19,0:02:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,put to death by the sword in 44 C.E.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.10,0:02:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Remembering the loyalty\Nand the courage of these brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.10,0:02:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,would have been a benefit\Nto the brothers in the congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.54,0:02:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,especially as the end\Nof the Jewish system drew near.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.71,0:02:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now,\Nhow can we apply Paul’s exhortation today?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.42,0:02:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,As the {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}Watchtower {\r} comments mention,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.15,0:02:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,one way is to remember\Nand imitate the example
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.69,0:02:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,of our faithful members\Nof the Governing Body.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.06,0:03:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And just as members\Nof the Jerusalem congregation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.06,0:03:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,we at Bethel\Nhave an extraordinary privilege
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.90,0:03:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and a unique opportunity to see the faith
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.64,0:03:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and observe the conduct\Nof our brothers on the Governing Body.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.14,0:03:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And today, by means of JW Broadcasting®,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.55,0:03:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,our brothers around the world
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.72,0:03:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,actually see members of the Governing Body,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.29,0:03:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,they hear them speak the Word of God to them,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.49,0:03:30.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and they can observe their conduct.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.09,0:03:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And also we have the life stories
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.73,0:03:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of former members of the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.00,0:03:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,who faithfully served Jehovah for decades
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.47,0:03:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,until they received their heavenly reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.71,0:03:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s just remember four of them
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.94,0:03:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and what they told us\Nabout ‘how their conduct turned out.’
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.65,0:03:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The first is T. J. Sullivan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.62,0:03:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Brother Sullivan\Nfaithfully served on the Governing Body
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.96,0:04:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,until his death in 1974.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.79,0:04:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In his life story\Nin {\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}The Watchtower {\r} of August 15, 1965,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.60,0:04:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Sullivan related \Nwhat happened at Madison Square Garden
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.47,0:04:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in June of 1939.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.34,0:04:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Rutherford was giving a talk
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.64,0:04:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,when a demon-controlled mob\Ntried to break up that meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.48,0:04:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A number of brothers were falsely arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.68,0:04:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen to his comments:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.68,0:04:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“Brother Rutherford insisted on going
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.95,0:04:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“to the police station immediately . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.06,0:04:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,“I was privileged to drive\Nalong with him on that occasion.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.16,0:04:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“Driving through\Nfrom the Madison Square Garden
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.83,0:04:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“to the police station,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.66,0:04:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,“we saw demonstrated\Nthe mad fury of the mob
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.73,0:04:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“and the restraining power of our God
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.87,0:04:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“to preserve his people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.50,0:04:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“At the police station we had to struggle
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.54,0:04:52.91,Default,,0,0,0,,through the mob to get in.”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.91,0:04:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So after assisting the brothers\Nand on leaving the police station,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.95,0:04:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Sullivan added:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.58,0:05:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,“On our leaving,\Nthe same demonic mob was still outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.12,0:05:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“They tried to force their way\Ninto the car and bar its progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.76,0:05:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“It was necessary for some of us\Nto ride on the running boards
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.96,0:05:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep the crowds\Nfrom tearing the doors open.”
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.03,0:05:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What courage!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.37,0:05:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What boldness\NBrothers Rutherford and Sullivan displayed!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.01,0:05:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Will we need to display\Nsuch courage in the days ahead?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.21,0:05:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, let’s remember\NBrother George Gangas,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.05,0:05:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,another former member\Nof the Governing Body.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.98,0:05:34.98,Default,,0,0,0,,His life story appeared
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.98,0:05:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,in the October 15, 1966, W{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}atchtower.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.72,0:05:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever felt inadequate\Nfor assignments you were given?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.09,0:05:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Gangas related what happened
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.30,0:05:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,when he gave his first six-minute talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.07,0:05:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He was gripped with fear\Nand could hardly finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.50,0:05:55.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But he never quit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.04,0:05:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He also set a wonderful example\Nin his love for the meetings.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.08,0:06:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He prayed to God\Nto not permit him to miss any meetings,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.01,0:06:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and for 45 years up to that point,\Nhe had not.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.15,0:06:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He said:\N“To me, meeting with the brothers
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.06,0:06:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“is one of life’s greatest pleasures
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.76,0:06:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,“and a source of encouragement.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.13,0:06:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,“I love to be at the Kingdom Hall\Namong the first,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.16,0:06:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,“and leave among the last,\Nif possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.77,0:06:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“I feel an inward joy\Nwhen talking with God’s people.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.14,0:06:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“When I am among them\NI feel at home with my family,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.14,0:06:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,in a spiritual paradise.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.58,0:06:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Gangas\Nfinished his earthly course
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.18,0:06:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in 1994 at 98 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.25,0:06:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we remember
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.59,0:06:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Karl Klein.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.72,0:06:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He related that on one occasion,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.73,0:06:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Rutherford gave him a blunt reproof.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.60,0:06:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The next time he saw Karl,\Nhe cheerily said, “Hello, Karl.”
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.10,0:07:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But because of still feeling hurt,\NKarl just muttered a greeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.74,0:07:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Rutherford continued:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.74,0:07:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,“Karl, watch out! The Devil’s after you!”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.11,0:07:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Embarrassed, he replied,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.15,0:07:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“Oh, there’s nothing, Brother Rutherford.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.85,0:07:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But he knew better\Nand repeated his warning:
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.82,0:07:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“That’s all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.99,0:07:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Just watch out. The Devil’s after you.”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.92,0:07:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we should remember\Nthese words of Brother Klein
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.93,0:07:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,because they are Bible-based.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.93,0:07:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Never do we want\Nto “allow place for the Devil”
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.97,0:07:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,by harboring resentment.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.57,0:07:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In January 2001 at the age of 95,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.87,0:07:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl Klein\Nfaithfully completed his earthly course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.44,0:07:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we remember Brother Dan Sydlik.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.11,0:07:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Sydlik’s life story appeared\Nin the June 1, 1985, Wat{\i1}{\fs18}{\fnSerif}chtower. 
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.69,0:07:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,We were always encouraged
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.36,0:07:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,when Brother Sydlik\Nwould start his morning worship
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.49,0:07:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,with a hearty, “It’s good to be alive
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.86,0:08:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to serve the true and loving God, Jehovah.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.27,0:08:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,His story reveals\Nwhy Brother Sydlik loved life,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.24,0:08:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,loved God’s people, loved Jehovah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.27,0:08:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He wrote:\N“Throughout life’s experiences, . . .
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.34,0:08:17.71,Default,,0,0,0,,there has been the ever-sustaining power\Nof God’s friendship.”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.71,0:08:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He added:\N“Even at this moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.28,0:08:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“sheer joy overwhelms me 
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.79,0:08:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,“when I read\Nthe psalmist’s words [in Psalm 33]:
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.42,0:08:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Happy the nation\Nthat has Jehovah for its God,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.10,0:08:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘the people that he chose as his estate!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.97,0:08:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘. . . Let your friendship\Nbe over us, Jehovah,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.14,0:08:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,as we rest our expectations on you.’”
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.14,0:08:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Sydlik\Nfinished his earthly course in April 2006
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.68,0:08:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,after having served at Bethel\Nfor nearly 60 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.08,0:08:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, brothers, we do well to remember
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.69,0:09:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,both the current and former members\Nof the Governing Body.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.09,0:09:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,As was the case with the Jewish Christians\Nto whom Paul wrote,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.69,0:09:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,we too are approaching\Nthe end of a system of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.43,0:09:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we need to imitate the faith
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.10,0:09:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of our brothers who take the lead among us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.91,0:09:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And that will help us endure to the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.51,0:09:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,whether that end is the end of our life now
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.51,0:09:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,or the end of this wicked system of things.
